description: Iggy Pop (April 21, 1947) is an American singer, songwriter, musician, and actor. Though widely known as an innovator and "godfather" of punk rock,[1] Pop's music has encompassed a number of styles over the years, including pop, hard rock, jazz and blues.Pop became known as 'Iggy' in high school, during which time he served as drummer for local blues band The Iguanas.
